{"parse":{"title":"The Spirit of Spanish Music","pageid":53320920,"revid":806358684,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:312px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg/310px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg\" width=\"310\" height=\"188\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg/465px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg/620px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4417\" data-file-height=\"2676\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_3.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> in the Lebus Court of the Mabel Shaw Bridges Hall of Music. <a href=\"/wiki/Pomona_College\" title=\"Pomona College\">Pomona College</a>, Claremont, California, USA.</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>The Spirit of Spanish Music</b></i> is a sculpture by\n<a href=\"/wiki/Burt_Johnson\" title=\"Burt Johnson\">Burt William Johnson</a> (25 April 1890\u201427 March 1927<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>).\nIt was commissioned by the <a href=\"/wiki/Pomona_College\" title=\"Pomona College\">Pomona College</a> class of 1915<sup id=\"cite_ref-timeline_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-timeline-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and\nplaced in the Lebus Court of the Mabel Shaw Bridges Hall of Music at <a href=\"/wiki/Pomona_College\" title=\"Pomona College\">Pomona College</a>, one of a\ngroup of buildings conceived for the expansion of Pomona College and built in the mid-1910s by\narchitect <a href=\"/wiki/Myron_Hunt\" title=\"Myron Hunt\">Myron Hunt</a> using details of the \"ornamental Spanish style\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:312px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg/310px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg\" width=\"310\" height=\"226\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg/465px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg/620px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1661\" data-file-height=\"1211\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spanish_music_1916-02-10_2.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Burt W. Johnson, working in his studio in February, 1916 on the model for <i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i>, in a snapshot inscribed for Pomona College Pres. Blaisdell and signed by the sculptor.</div></div></div>\n<p>This style, and the fact that the building where it stands was intended\nfor the study and performance of music, give the sculpture its name.\n(Other names for the sculpture sometimes are seen in various sources, including \n<i><b>Pastoral Flutist</b></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Master_Plan_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Master_Plan-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and <i><b>Youth</b></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Country_Life_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Country_Life-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>)\n</p><p>The figure itself, a boy in \"classic contrapposto stance\"\nplaying an elongated flute, was influenced by the 15th century Florentine sculptor \n<a href=\"/wiki/Desiderio_da_Settignano\" title=\"Desiderio da Settignano\">Desiderio da Settignano</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Centennial_Lecture_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Centennial_Lecture-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\nIt reflects the overall \"Arcadian\" theme Hunt intended for Pomona's south campus.<sup id=\"cite_ref-timeline_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-timeline-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The sculpture's harmony with the building surrounding its courtyard setting\nwas described in 1921 as \"happily eloquent of the spirit of the place\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Country_Life_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Country_Life-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n\"The pose is exquisite,\" reports another journal of the period,\n\"and the design peculiarly appropriate to the Spanish architecture of the beautiful\ntemple of music it is to adorn.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-The_Pacific_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-The_Pacific-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\nIn a lecture on the occasion of the Centennial in 2015 of the statue and the building,\nart historian George L. Gorse labels the setting \"A Pastoral Theatre\", and characterizes\nthe sculpture as \"Vergilian 'Arcadia' . . . absolutely Vergilian.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Centennial_Lecture_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Centennial_Lecture-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The sculpture was cast in bronze by the <a href=\"/wiki/Gorham_Manufacturing_Company\" title=\"Gorham Manufacturing Company\">Gorham Company</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Providence,_Rhode_Island\" title=\"Providence, Rhode Island\">Providence, R.I.</a> It is life-size, \napproximately 137&#160;cm (54 in.) in height. Before being delivered to Claremont and installed in\nLebus Court, it was exhibited by the <a href=\"/wiki/Gorham_Manufacturing_Company\" title=\"Gorham Manufacturing Company\">Gorham Company</a> at their gallery on Fifth Avenue in New York, and at the Winter Exhibition at the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Academy_Museum_and_School\" title=\"National Academy Museum and School\">National Academy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-The_Pacific_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-The_Pacific-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After part of the fountain collapsed, the statue was removed in early 2015 while repairs were made.\nBefore its return on 14 August 2015, <i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> was restored by conservator Donna Williams, including the repair of the boy's broken flute.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Blackstock_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Blackstock-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Spirit_of_Spanish_Music&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg/100px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg\" width=\"100\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg/150px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg/200px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3291\" data-file-height=\"3947\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> (aka <i>Pastoral Flutist</i>), 1916, restored 2015\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg/79px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg\" width=\"79\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg/118px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg/158px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2764\" data-file-height=\"4193\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> (aka <i>Pastoral Flutist</i>), 1916, restored 2015\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:27.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg/120px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"95\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg/180px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg/240px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_4.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3923\" data-file-height=\"3099\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> (aka <i>Pastoral Flutist</i>), 1916, restored 2015\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:52.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg/120px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"45\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg/180px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg/240px-Johnson_spanish_music_1916_inscriptions.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3600\" data-file-height=\"1350\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Inscriptions on the pedestal of <i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> (aka <i>Pastoral Flutist</i>), 1916, restored 2015\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:39.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg/120px-Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"71\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg/180px-Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg/240px-Johnson_burt_spanish_music_1916_5.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3708\" data-file-height=\"2196\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>A small group of women and men stand in Lebus Court, Mabel Shaw Bridges Hall of Music (c.1920), viewing Burt W. Johnson's 1916 sculpture, <i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i>, a gift of Pomona College Class of 1915\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:31.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg/120px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"87\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg/180px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg/240px-Spanish_music_1916-02-10_1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1656\" data-file-height=\"1201\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Studio snapshot of plaster working model of <i>The Spirit of Spanish Music</i> (1916)\"\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.sv